Rating: 3
The sauce is similar to a Bon Appetite recipe of grilled pork tenderloin in mustard cream sauce (vintage 1990). Only this sauce is low in fat. It was excellent. I recommend green beans as an accompaniment and mushroom risotto. I sauteed the chicken coated with a panko/parmesean breading in two tablespoons of olive oil. Place that on the warmer and deglaze the pan with a small onion (red), shallot--not too large, and the garlic in recipe. I squirted in some fine mustard, about 1/4 cup of white wine and chicken broth--low sodium. Let that saute a bit, then slip the chicken back on top, cover and simmer 10 minutes--coating will not be crisp, but it tastes good. Put the whole thing on the warmer, get everything else together and serve.

