I thought that this dish was very good. It has simple but delicious ingriedients when integrated with each other and the chicken is beyond tender when it's done. If you would like a side dish with this then you can have chipotle yams. Mash your yams after cooking them whichever way you want. Then add a tbs. of butter and a pinch of salt. Then mince one chipotle pepper and add. If you want milder yams add 1 teaspoon adobo sauce (it's in the can of chipotle peppers), 2 tbs. if you're somewhere in the middle, and if you're like me then you'll want 3 tbs. But be sparing with the sauce as it really is HOT! You may want to just start with 1-2 teaspoon as a safety precaution for the good of your health. By the way, I got this recipefrom Good Eats (w/ Alton Brown, of course). Good show!

