I think it was all of the controversy presented in the varied reviews of this dish that prompted me to try it. I had never poached chicken before - in fact, I don't think I'd knowingly even eaten poached chicken (the thought of meat cooked in liquid was just a little too strange) but I gave it a try and was VERY impressed with the results. I must admit, I cheated - I quickly browned the chicken and sauteed the onions and garlic before adding the liquids. The texture of the chicken was perfect and the sauce came out great. I actually doubled everthing (except the mustard) and added a healthy splash of white wine, despite the fact that I was only using 4 breasts, and ended up with just enough sauce (I would've liked even more - it was really that good). Easy, healthy, cheap weeknight chicken recipe (and it got me over my fear of poaching). I'll make it again, this time with enough for substantial leftovers as the little I had were great the next day.

