Rating: 3
An incredibly easy and succulent dish that was well received by children and adults alike! Unlike others who prefer to brown the chicken first, I find this recipe lends itself suitable to poaching and is similiar in feel to poached tarragon chicken in its elegant appearance. I also heeded the advice of another reviewer and added 1 1/2 cups chicken broth when I was cooking 8 breasts and still found the liquid too much. 1 cup broth to 8 breast proportion would be fine which would make 2/3 cup to 8 breasts about fine. Also 1/2 large white onion to 6 breasts would be fine as I used about 2/3 to 8 breasts and found the chicken very flavorful. I also added 1 TBS of flour (less if you use less broth) which gives a wonderful creamy texture to the sauce and falls elegantly over the chicken breasts One other tip from professional cooking: in poaching chicken I cut a circle from parchment paper size of pan, spray it with Pam and lay it directly on top of chicken and simmer it that way without pot cover and you get a very moist well flavored chicken done in exactly 20 minutes on low heat (#3 on electric stovetop) Goes great with broccoli!

